  "prompt": "How much bands needs to get admission in UC berkeley for indian student after 12th?",
  "response": "Admission to the University of California, Berkeley (UC Berkeley) for undergraduate programs is highly competitive. For Indian students and other international applicants, the admission requirements can vary by program, but the general expectations include:\n\n1. **Academic Performance:** A strong academic record, including high grades in core subjects. A competitive GPA is typically essential.\n\n2. **Standardized Tests:** As of recent admissions cycles, UC Berkeley has adopted a test-blind policy, meaning that they do not consider SAT or ACT scores in their admissions process. This policy applies to both domestic and international students. However, it is always good to check the latest updates on standardized testing requirements directly from the UC Berkeley admissions website.\n\n3. **English Proficiency Tests:** Non-native English speakers must demonstrate English proficiency, usually through tests like the TOEFL (Test of English as a Foreign Language) or IELTS (International English Language Testing System). UC Berkeley typically requires:\n   - A minimum TOEFL score of 80 (internet-based test) \n   - A minimum IELTS score of 6.5\n\n4. **Essays and Personal Insight Questions:** UC Berkeley requires students to respond to personal insight questions as part of the application. These essays are crucial for showcasing your personality, interests, and motivations.\n\n5. **Extracurricular Activities:** Involvement in extracurricular activities, leadership roles, and community service can strengthen your application.\n\n6. **Recommendation Letters:** While not required, strong letters of recommendation can support your application, particularly from teachers or mentors who know you well.\n\n7. **Portfolio:** Some specific programs, especially in the arts, may require a portfolio of your work.\n\nGiven the competitive nature of UC Berkeley admissions, there's no specific \"cut-off\" band or score, as decisions are made holistically. It\u2019s advisable to aim for excellence in all the above components to enhance your chances of admission. For the most current and specific requirements, always refer to the official UC Berkeley admissions website.\n",
